column5: Heading up that way tomorrow, looking at the regs book the lake is right on the border.  Am I limited to crappie fishing on friday or can I target pike and eyes? Any help is appreciated, can't find any info.
Awesome I thought so, thanks man
I might be out there sat trying my luck for pike. Might be a brutal day as my brothers coworkers 3of em have never fished before and are tagging along
I've got pliers on my boat if you need help removing any treble hooks, gf and I will be in late model (see pos) blue bayliner.

Its not that I'm worried about. Worried about my rods. And having to fix and retie everyone's lines and teaching them how to cast. I'll be in a lund impact, if I see you I'll wave. Its the first time I fish this lake. I'll prob be on the west side

I've fished it once before later in the season lots of pike, didn't do to good on the bass though I can point you to a couple spots.  Be ready for a zoo there will be tons of boat traffic this weekend.

Ya I figured, being part of the Trent and all. I've done well on kashe so hoping its similar. If you don't mind pm'ing me general areas, it be greatly appreciated. I normally always fish the kawarthas but I figured pike would be an easier catch then walleye so I don't bore my guests
Duck bay,fish the deep weeds and drop. Work your way out from there.
Changed my mind. Heading to couchiching. Still unfamiliar but I'll find em. Thanks for the help guys
